name: Invesco FTSE RAFI U.S. Index ETF
longDescription: PXU seeks to replicate, to the extent reasonably possible and before fees and expenses, the performance of the FTSE RAFI US 1000 Index, or any successor thereto, on an unhedged basis, in the case of any unhedged units, or on a hedged basis, in the case of any hedged units. Invesco FTSE RAFI U.S. Index ETF (the ETF) seeks to replicate, before fees and expenses, the performance of its underlying index, the FTSE RAFI US 1000 Index, on an unhedged basis, in the case of any unhedged units, or on a hedged basis, in the case of any hedged units.
fulldescription: PXU seeks to replicate, to the extent reasonably possible and before fees and expenses, the performance of the FTSE RAFI US 1000 Index, or any successor thereto, on an unhedged basis, in the case of any unhedged units, or on a hedged basis, in the case of any hedged units. Invesco FTSE RAFI U.S. Index ETF (the ETF) seeks to replicate, before fees and expenses, the performance of its underlying index, the FTSE RAFI US 1000 Index, on an unhedged basis, in the case of any unhedged units, or on a hedged basis, in the case of any hedged units. This ETF gives investors exposure to the 1,000 highest fundamentally weighted U.S. equities with the highest fundamental weightings using the Fundamental Index methodology developed by Research Affiliates, LLC.
